metadata.name: Dime-A-Dozen
metadata.description:
Dime-A-Dozen

Focuses on women's Mental Health.

Expresses the message of how women are expected to live up to "Society Standards" which can lead to them not being comfortable within their own bodies and struggle to express their "true colors"

What this piece resembles is something that is very relevant in today's society and not only occurs in women but also in men, something that everybody deals with at one point in time, trying to find their true selves but being shot down by society, causing them to be unable to reach those goals.

Part 1 of Society's Paradigm
